				\begin{document}$${\text{slope}} = {\text{nkT}}/q$$\end{document}where k stands for the Boltzmann constant, T represents the absolute temperature, and q denotes the elementary charge. Compared with the control device (1.62), the devices with KCl, KMS, KTFSI and KFSI realized lower n values of 1.56, 1.39, 1.30 and 1.20, respectively, which is indicative of memorably restrained non-radiative recombination, agreeing with the above TPV results. The exponential relationship between JSC and light intensity is also shown in Fig. S17 and the exponential factor α of the KFSI modified device (0.979) was highest, followed by the device with KTFSI (0.968), the device with KMS (0.956), the device with KCl (0.950), and the control device (0.948). This indicates that KFSI modified device showed efficient carrier transport and extraction.Fig. 4
